    "audio": "http://seattleunity.org/podcasts/Seattle-Unity-12_03_17-The-Adventure-Begins.mp3",
    "audio_length": 3755,
    "description_y": "<p><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-28841\" src=\"http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"350\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-1.jpg 350w, http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-1-240x220.jpg 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" />Rev. Karen welcomed in the Advent season, a cross-cultural time of calling back the light. She discussed Mary&#8217;s saying &#8220;yes&#8221; to the angel Gabriel, and its metaphysical meaning.</p>\n<p>Mary, Rev. Karen explained, represents our intuitive self, When we trust and listen to this part of us, we can go forward with our lives in choosing life-affirming challenges.</p>\n<p>The Holy Spirit (the activity of God within) can, and probably has, come upon each of us at least once &#8211; and how did we respond to that inner call?</p>\n<p>Our wonderfully talented Home Team gifted us in musical selections today. Listen for that &#8220;yes&#8221;&#8230;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-28840\" src=\"http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"493\" srcset=\"http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-2.jpg 600w, http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-2-240x197.jpg 240w, http://seattleunity.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sunday-20171203-2-487x400.jpg 487w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
