    "audio_length": 5781,
    "description_y": "Episode 41 of #TwoWiseJawns is available for your listening pleasure on Apple Podcasts, Stitcher, Google Play, and SoundCloud.\n\n\"She's Gotta Have It\" was Spike Lee's insightful 1986 film about a liberated woman extolling her self-expression and reclaiming her time! \n..by wasting other people's tehe. \n\nWhy must dating always be so zero-sum!\n\nThis episode we discuss the 2017 take on \"She's Gotta Have It\" which premiered on Netflix Thanksgiving Day as a series. \n\nThanks to Nola Darling, we deep dive into the themes of sexuality, relationships, compromise, feminist mystique, millennial angst, gentrification, and more. \nAnd of course we rank our favorite suitors of hers -- Opal, Mars, Jamie, Greer. \n\nFinally, we apologize for excluding Lady Raqueletta Moss from the narrative. She was in the notes! We got carried away Iyanla'ing Nola and blocked our blessings. \n\nHOT TOPICS:\n- Migrant crisis and stability vacuum facilitate slavery in Libya and the region.\n- Morgan's prediction that Rihanna would marry Prince Harry is false (for now). He's decided on another sis of the diaspora, Miss Meghan Markle. \n- Naya Rivera is a domestic abuser -- Santana Lopez would not go out like this... okay she would, but still. \n- David Ortunga is waving his Men's Rights flag -- wins primary custody of his and Jennifer Hudson's child. \n- Joyner Lucas may not be racist but he ain't it either. \n- Ann Curry sipped champagne and the finest Beluga caviar upon the news of Matt Lauer's termination from The Today Show. \n- Kim Kardashian is the Social Justice Warrior we need -- hired a top lawyer for Cyntoia Brown. \n- Lt. General Michael Flynn dropped names! Means nothing. Trump is the Teflon Don apparently. \n- The House and Senate passed the GOP Tax Plan and it's peak Republican. \n\n\nRecorded Sunday, December 3, 2017.",
