    "audio_length": 4004,
    "description_y": "Are you familiar with Larry Fassenden's indie arctic horror THE LAST WINTER? How about the found footage conspiracy theory laden DEVIL'S PASS? Neither had we, but we've been freezing our butts off lately and sat down with 2 creepy, cold horror films. \n\nJoin Kim and Jon on this week's episode of Nightmare on Film Street as they discuss the secrets of Russia's mountainside in DEVIL'S PASS (2013) and the end of the world in THE LAST WINTER (2006). \n\nWhat's Keeping us Creepy?\n\n\t1. Have you ever wondered how HOME ALONE or MIRACLE ON 34TH STREET could have been remade as a horror movie? We horror-ify your favorite Christmas movies on the NOFS blog at  https://tinyurl.com/ycfzto23\n\t2. Bonus review! We talk POOL PARTY MASSACRE (2017)\n\t3. NOFS ENAMEL PINS ARE NOW IN STOCK! GET YOURS TODAY AT: www.store.nofspodcast.com\n\nAs always, cast your vote in our Winter Horrorland Twitter Poll @NOFSpodcast, and join our facebook group to continue the conversation with horror fiends like yourself.\n\n----------\nNightmare on Film Street is made possible because of fiends like yourself!\nSupport the show at https://www.patreon.com/nightmareonfilmstreet",
