    "image": "http://is3.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music71/v4/77/d5/7d/77d57d67-acf1-2fc2-d070-6c31e0135752/source/600x600bb.jpg",
    "description_x": "A weekly after-show series that breaks down episodes of Bravo’s Real Housewives of Beverly Hills, Real Housewives of New York City, Real Housewives of Orange County and Real Housewives of Dallas. During the hiatus weeks our hosts will discuss news & announcements pertaining to these Housewives shows as well as the other franchises. Throughout the series we'll bring in guests to join in on the fun!",
    "language": "English",
    "categories": "TV & Film",
    "website": "http://www.afterbuzztv.com/aftershows/real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-afterbuzztv-aftershow/",
    "author": "AfterBuzz TV Network",
    "itunes_id": 863874076,
    "title_y": "Real Housewives of Beverly Hills S:8 | Stronger Than Ever E:1 | AfterBuzz TV AfterShow",
    "audio": "http://podtrac.com/pts/redirect.mp3/audio.afterbuzztv.com/media/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/RH_BH_S08_E01_Mixdown.mp3",
    "audio_length": 1856,
    "description_y": "<p>AFTERBUZZ TV — The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills edition, is a weekly &#8220;after show&#8221; for fans of Bravo&#8217;s The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills. In this episode hosts Richie Skye, Thomas Orlina, and Jennifer Leon break down episode 1.</p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT REAL HOUSEWIVES OF BEVERLY HILLS:</strong><br />\nThe Real Housewives of Beverly Hills (abbreviated <i><b>RHOBH</b></i>) is an American <a title=\"Reality television\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reality_television\">reality television</a> series that premiered on October 14, 2010 on <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bravo (U.S. TV channel)\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bravo_(U.S._TV_channel)\">Bravo</a>. Developed as the sixth installment of <i><a title=\"The Real Housewives\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Real_Housewives\">The Real Housewives</a></i> franchise, following <i><a title=\"The Real Housewives of Orange County\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Real_Housewives_of_Orange_County\">The Real Housewives of Orange County</a></i>, <i><a title=\"The Real Housewives of New York City\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Real_Housewives_of_New_York_City\">New York City</a></i>, <i><a title=\"The Real Housewives of Atlanta\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Real_Housewives_of_Atlanta\">Atlanta</a></i>, <i><a title=\"The Real Housewives of New Jersey\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Real_Housewives_of_New_Jersey\">New Jersey</a></i>, and <i><a title=\"The Real Housewives of D.C.\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Real_Housewives_of_D.C.\">D.C.</a></i>, it has aired four complete seasons and focuses on the personal and professional lives of several women residing in <a title=\"Beverly Hills, California\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beverly_Hills,_California\">Beverly Hills, California</a>.</p>\n<p>The series originally focused on <a title=\"Taylor Armstrong\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor_Armstrong\">Taylor Armstrong</a>, <a title=\"Camille Grammer\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camille_Grammer\">Camille Grammer</a>, <a title=\"Adrienne Maloof\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adrienne_Maloof\">Adrienne Maloof</a>, <a title=\"Kim Richards\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Richards\">Kim Richards</a>, <a title=\"Kyle Richards\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyle_Richards\">Kyle Richards</a>, and <a title=\"Lisa Vanderpump\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lisa_Vanderpump\">Lisa Vanderpump</a>. Grammer transitioned into a recurring role beginning in the third season and was replaced by <a title=\"Brandi Glanville\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandi_Glanville\">Brandi Glanville</a>, who was upgraded, and newcomer <a title=\"Yolanda Foster\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yolanda_Foster\">Yolanda Foster</a>. Armstrong and Maloof departed the series at the conclusion of the third season; <a title=\"Joyce Giraud\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joyce_Giraud\">Joyce Giraud de Ohoven</a> and Carlton Gebbia were introduced in their absences during the fourth season. Gebbia and Giraud de Ohoven departed the series at the conclusion of the fourth season and were replaced by <a title=\"Eileen Davidson\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eileen_Davidson\">Eileen Davison</a> and <a title=\"Lisa Rinna\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lisa_Rinna\">Lisa Rinna</a> in the fifth season.</p>\n<p>Follow us on <a href=\"http://www.Twitter.com/AfterBuzzTV\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">http://www.Twitter.com/AfterBuzzTV</a><br />\n&#8220;Like&#8221; Us on <a href=\"http://www.Facebook.com/AfterBuzzTV\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">http://www.Facebook.com/AfterBuzzTV</a><br />\nBuy Merch at <a href=\"http://shop.spreadshirt.com/AfterbuzzTV/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">http://shop.spreadshirt.com/AfterbuzzTV/</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.afterbuzztv.com/2017/12/19/real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-s8-stronger-than-ever-e1-afterbuzz-tv-aftershow/\">Real Housewives of Beverly Hills S:8 | Stronger Than Ever E:1 | AfterBuzz TV AfterShow</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.afterbuzztv.com\">AfterBuzz TV Network</a>.</p>",
