    "title_y": "Is Sexual Harassment Becoming Trivialized?",
    "audio": "http://www.blogtalkradio.com/ourownvoices/2017/12/04/is-sexual-harassment-becoming-trivialized.mp3",
    "audio_length": 3600,
    "description_y": "Welcome to Our Own Voices Live with your hosts: Angela Thomas & Rodney Smith\n\nOur Topic(s) today: “Is Sexual Harassment becoming Trivialized?”\n\nIf you have a question, comment or just want to listen, give us a call: (347) 826-9600. Press #1 to speak\n\nIs Sexual Harassment becoming Trivialized?\n\nThis week allegations of sexual harassment against another democratic elected official have been made.  The range is from freshmen congressmen, a former comedian to the dean of Congress.  There has been a major awareness initiative called #MeToo that has acted as a wave over the country.  Many entertainers and business leaders have stepped down or have been fired.  Matt Lauer was fired Tuesday.  Prior to him it was Bill O’Reilly and others in the news media.  It seems to be a low tolerance for it in the business and entertainment world but not so much in the political arena.  In spite of calls for resignations most are still there from the President to the latest Congressperson. Are politicians serious when they call for another to resign or maybe it’s just political cover?  It seems that our moral compass is rolling back due to political tribalism that has run a muck!  Is this really a big moment for sexual harassment victims or is Sexual Harassment becoming Trivialized?\n\nIf you have a question, comment or just want to listen, give us a call: (347) 826-9600. Press #1 to speak\n\n \n\nOur Own Voices Live is a radio show featuring people and stories from our community in Las Vegas, the surrounding area and some place near you. America is the greatest country on earth due to its cultural diversity and not in spite of it. Our mission is to help bridge the cultural and ethnic divide in America by working together to build the greatest bridge in history to unite us",
