    "description_y": "Non-fiction & Family Life Book Showcase \n\n\tGenres: Christian fiction, Children books, business, poetry, political, medical and self-help. Here are the authors and speakers invited to the program. The radio shows take place each night from 8-10pm EST.  Join Ella Curry and 40+ authors in the BAN Radio Chatroom as we celebrate 10 years of service! Our publishing friends have donated over 200 books for the readers and several other book related gifts. Meet us in the chatroom over the next 5 days to receive your gift book!\n\n\n\t \nThursday night, December 7 - Monday night, December 11, 2017 there will be book giveaways in the BAN Radio Chatroom. You have to be in the chatroom to receive your copies. This is going to be so much fun. Tell all of your friends!  I would love to meet all of my clients from 2007-2017 in the chatroom!  \n\n\nF\n\n\tBlack Books Weekend Day 1 -  http://tobtr.com/s/10447697\n\tFeatured Authors, Speakers and Community Leaders\n\t \n\t- Black Cotton by Tomeekha Pitre  \n\t- Is It Nighttime, Nina? by Zanetta Tribble\n\t- Multicultural Children’s Books by Quentin Holmes  \n\t - Zach and His Cat by Vera Harris \n\t- Longtale Children's Books by Duane Filer\n\t- Soul Movement with Cheryl Polote Williamson\n\t- Carver Park by Dr. Lynda J. Mubarak  \n\t- Nandi's Unexpected Gift by Ama Kuma \n\t- The Hair Adventures of Princess Lindsey Sidney by Eartha Dunston\n\t- Turning Trials Into Triumphs by Michelle Chavis, Venita Alderman Sadler and Shavonna Futrell",
