    "audio_length": 2941,
    "description_y": "<img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848.jpg\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" alt=\"modus operandi brunswick beer collective\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;max-width: 100%;\" srcset=\"https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848.jpg 800w, https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848-300x200.jpg 300w, https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848-768x512.jpg 768w, https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848-298x199.jpg 298w, https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848-360x240.jpg 360w, https://thecitylane.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5848-750x500.jpg 750w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" itemprop=\"image\" /><p>PODCAST | In this season-opening episode, we attempt to make up for the postponed Brewers Feast beer festival by instead chronicling Paul and Ben&#8217;s incredible journey through Sydney&#8217;s Northern Beaches, in which they apparently end up largely at <a href=\"http://4pinesbeer.com.au/\">4 Pines</a> venues. It&#8217;s a wander that involves buses, tiny breweries, Google definitions, and the delicate art of crashing a Christmas party for a Boxing club. It also explores the incredible amount of 4 Pines Breweries in Sydney, and may well confirm our dream of bringing back the fabled Guava Gose from the aforementioned brewery.</p>\n<p>And if that wasn&#8217;t enough, we talk about Chris&#8217; love of the Modus Operandi Red IPA, the Former Tenant, discuss the first time we drank it, and reluctantly let Chris talk excessively about his complimentary article about the beer in <a href=\"http://frothbeer.com/\">Froth Craft Beer Magazine</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Featured beers:</strong> Sonic Prayer, Former Tenant, and Future Factory by <a href=\"http://www.mobrewing.com.au/\">Modus Operandi Brewing Co.</a></p>",
