    "description_y": "<p>Write into Jules and Sarah! The Port Salut Crew HQ, PO Box 66747, London, NW5 9GH – we love your letters! Gosh it’s good to hear the mumbles of a Manchester crowd isn’t it?! Nestled in with the Port Salut Crew of the northern hub, Jules and Sarah kick off with tales of Jules’ flat tyre, his oglings of cute Manchester boys, and a new discovery and shift in silhouette to a wide leg trouser. Ever present at a podcast live, June comes this week complete with her own home made (kind of) chutney. Sarah and June decide to skip Slimming World for mash potato (with chips) this week. Correspondence is live letters from the audience this week – whoop! Shelagh is in turmoil with an opera recital whilst June has difficulty in an Aldi carpark. News from The North involves a duck who’s outlived expectations and is kicking back, along with a cheese factory jobs board.</p><p><br></p><p>For those Port Salut Crew members who joined in with this recording, we love you. </p><p>A special thanks to Port Salut and Babybel for providing such a fantastic spread and to Odd Bar in Manchester for hosting this event xx</p><p><br></p><p>@julesandsarahpodcast</p><p>@julesvonhep</p><p>@thissarahpowell</p><p><br></p><p>Listen to the Jules and Sarah Mixtape on Spotify! http://bit.ly/JulesandSarah</p>",
